WEBVTT

00:00:01.570 --> 00:00:14.928
Ancient Faith Radio presents Homilies from All Saints, taken from the weekly sermons by Father Patrick Henry Reardon, priest at All Saints Orthodox Church in Chicago and senior editor of Touchstone Magazine.

00:00:15.348 --> 00:00:16.210
Here's Father Pat.

00:00:17.671 --> 00:00:25.983
The reading is from the first epistle to the Corinthians beginning in chapter 13.

00:00:30.248 --> 00:00:31.570
Love never ends.

00:00:33.218 --> 00:00:35.060
As for prophecies, they will pass away.

00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:38.204
As for tongues, they will cease.

00:00:39.926 --> 00:00:41.649
As for knowledge, it will pass away.

00:00:41.689 --> 00:00:47.135
For our knowledge is imperfect and our prophecy is imperfect.

00:00:48.998 --> 00:00:52.562
But when the perfect comes, the imperfect will pass away.

00:00:55.246 --> 00:00:57.488
When I was a child, I spoke like a child.

00:00:58.129 --> 00:00:59.611
I thought like a child.

